summary:
The Security Council,
 Expressing desire for full and fair investigation into efforts by former Iraqi Government to evade sanctions through bribery and illicit payments,
Concerned by reports questioning administration of Oil-for-food Programme, including allegations of fraud and corruption,
Affirming that illicit activity by UN officials, personnel, agents, and contractors is unacceptable,
Emphasizing importance of full cooperation with independent inquiry,
 Welcomes appointment of independent high-level inquiry; 
Calls upon Coalition Provisional Authority, Iraq, and all Member States to cooperate fully with inquiry; 
Looks forward to receiving inquiryâ€™s final report; 
Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
